<assessment id="u4_m1_estimation2_tutor1">
    <title>Tutor</title>
    <question id="q1">
        <body>Based on survey results, the proportion of
            U<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101159-0500"?>.<?oxy_insert_end?>S<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101200-0500"?>.<?oxy_insert_end?>
            adults who use the
            <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101205-0500"?>I<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101205-0500" content="i"?>nternet
            on a daily basis is .37. This point estimate would be unbiased and most accurate if the
            survey was based on:</body>
        <multiple_choice shuffle="false">
            <choice value="A">a random sample of
                1<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101238-0500"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>000
                U<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101239-0500"?>.<?oxy_insert_end?>S<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101240-0500"?>.<?oxy_insert_end?>
                adults.</choice>
            <choice value="B">a random sample of
                2<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101245-0500"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>500
                U<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101247-0500"?>.<?oxy_insert_end?>S<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101247-0500"?>.<?oxy_insert_end?>
                adults.</choice>
            <choice value="C">a random sample of
                1<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101251-0500"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>000
                college students.</choice>
            <choice value="D">a random sample of
                2<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101255-0500"?>,<?oxy_insert_end?>500
                college students.</choice>
        </multiple_choice>
        <part>
            <response match="A">
                <feedback>Incorrect. While it is true that this estimate is based on a
                    random sample (and is therefore "on target"), recall that the larger the sample
                    that the estimate is based on the more accurate the estimate is. Try
                again.</feedback>
            </response>
            <response match="B" score="10">
                <feedback>Good
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101323-0500"?>j<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101323-0500" content="J"?>ob!
                    The estimate is based on a random sample (and is therefore
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101345-0500"?>unbiased<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101342-0500" content="&quot;on target&quot;"?>)
                    and is also based on a larger sample, which makes it more accurate.</feedback>
            </response>
            <response match="C">
                <feedback>Incorrect. Since the random sample consisted of only college
                    students (who probably use the
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101412-0500"?>I<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101412-0500" content="i"?>nternet
                    very frequently), our point estimate overestimates the true
                    proportion.<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101437-0500"?><?oxy_comment_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101509-0500" comment="addition OK?"?>
                    Also, a lar<?oxy_comment_end?>ger sample would be more
                    accurate.<?oxy_insert_end?></feedback>
            </response>
            <response match="D">
                <feedback>Incorrect. Since the random sample consisted of only college
                    students (who probably use the
                    <?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101425-0500"?>I<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101123T101424-0500" content="i"?>nternet
                    very frequently), our point estimate overestimates the true
                    proportion.</feedback>
            </response>
        </part>
